[SN]TITLE[SN]
Cardiff park fire: Man dies after suffering severe burns

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
A man has died after suffering severe burns in a fire in Cardiff.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
The 40-year-old was seen on fire at the Marl Recreation Ground in Grangetown on Saturday.
He was taken to Swansea's Morriston Hospital but died later that night.
Chf Insp Karl Eenmaa said: "I would like to thank all those who tried to help the man on Saturday because they were met with a horrific situation but acted selflessly and did whatever they could."
Police have confirmed they are not looking for anyone else in relation to the man's death.
Chf Insp Eenmaa added: "We are mindful that those who were there may be extremely disturbed by what they saw and should seek to get support if they need it."
